## First Run

```bash
go test ./...
go build -o bin/{{.ProjectName}} ./cmd/{{.ProjectName}}
plugin-kit-ai validate . --platform codex-runtime --strict
plugin-kit-ai test . --platform codex-runtime --event Notify
plugin-kit-ai dev . --platform codex-runtime --event Notify
```

The scaffold consumes `github.com/777genius/plugin-kit-ai/sdk@{{.GoSDKVersion}}` as a normal Go module release.

## Stable Default

- `Notify`

The scaffold wires the documented stable Codex `notify` path.

## Target Files

- `plugin/launcher.yaml`: runtime and entrypoint for local notify integration
- `plugin/targets/codex-runtime/package.yaml`: authored Codex runtime metadata
- `plugin/targets/codex-runtime/config.extra.toml`: optional passthrough for supported repo-local Codex config fields beyond managed `model` and `notify`
- `.codex/config.toml`: generated managed Codex config
- `fixtures/codex-runtime/Notify.json`: pre-generated stable Codex notify smoke payload owned by this project
- `goldens/codex-runtime/*`: pre-generated stable stdout/stderr/exit contract owned by this project

Keep stdout reserved for Codex responses and write diagnostics to stderr only.
